{
  "text": "The symptoms in Gulf veterans are similar to symptoms in other conflicts in that they share fatigue, shortness of breath, headache, sleep diYculties, impaired concentration, and forgetfulness. [CITATION_1] On first impressions, the Gulf War cannot compare with human casualties and settings of previous conflicts. On closer inspection, Gulf veterans were under considerable stress. The threat of biological and chemical warfare was real, constant, and serious and the associated fear cannot be underestimated. It has been argued that biological and chemical agents are as much psychological as physical weapons.",
